  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/fda-cdrh-vv40-review-panel",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors have been assessed. Achieved levels meet or exceed required levels across all factors, with three factors (Discretization Error, Numerical Solver Error, Model Inputs) exceeding their required gradation levels. The Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification (N=2000) demonstrates that the 95th-percentile NIH prediction remains below the clinical threshold of 0.1 g/100L at all five operating points within the COU operating envelope. The validation campaign used the same FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, representative fluid properties, and operating conditions spanning the COU envelope. Independent two-person review of the simulation setup confirmed no use errors. The provenance chain from raw experimental measurements through validation results to the credibility assessment is complete and traceable. The decision to accept the credibility evidence is supported by the structured 13-factor assessment, the Monte Carlo UQ results, and the quantitative validation metrics documented in the validation results. No credibility gaps remain unaddressed.",
